Description: Fragment of a small seal-impression made of fine brown Nile clay that was hardened after excavation. The rear shows a concave surface with impression of wood like from a bolt. In the break an impression of a turned cord with a width of 0.2 cm. The front shows a small oval impression of a scarab-like seal of which about the left half is preserved. It shows an oar (P8)? on top of a horizontal sign, to the right the central sign is broken away.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
